5. Downloading Files
Use wget to download a file from a URL (e.g., https://example.com/sample.txt).

Answer:
# 1. Use wget to download a file from a URL
wget https://example.com/sample.txt

# 2. Verify that the file was downloaded
ls -l sample.txt

# 3. Display the contents of the downloaded file
cat sample.txt

# 4. Clean up by removing the downloaded file
rm sample.txt

# 5. Verify that the file has been removed
ls -l sample.txt || echo "sample.txt has been removed"

# The final output should confirm that sample.txt has been removed